CCTV image released following theft from Pewsey shop
Updated 10:45am Tuesday 3rd May 2016 in
By Patrick McLean, Devizes reporter
FOLLOWING a theft from a local Pewsey shop, Wiltshire Police has released a CCTV image of the man wanted for questioning in connection with the incident.
It was reported a man entered the shop, Around the World,in North Street, at approximately 3pm on 7 April 2016, and told the store assistant that they had been advised by the owner that their mothers bag was being held in the cupboard at the back of the store after she accidentally left it there.
The store assistant went to the back of the store to look for the bag, but when she returned to the front of the shop, the man had left the shop. The shop assistant discovered that the till had been opened and 100 had been taken.
The man is being described as white, approximately six foot and two inches tall and of medium build. At the time of the incident he was wearing a hat and is described as being well spoken.
Anyone with information should call PSCO Jonathan Mills on 101, or alternatively Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111.
